author: Good Enough
description:
Rising over 8,000 meters in the Himalayas, Annapurna is a breathtaking giant with a terrifying reputation. With one of the highest fatality rates of any peak, this mountain has claimed the lives of countless climbers who dared to challenge its steep faces, unpredictable avalanches, and brutal weather. Annapurna is considered more dangerous than Mount Everest.
